text: The Buffy Fish Owl is a striking and rare species of owl that can be spotted in Singapore, particularly along the Ulu Pandan Outlet near the Ulu Pandan Canal. Known for its distinct ear tufts and yellow eyes, this owl prefers habitats near water bodies, where it hunts for fish. Birdwatchers flock to this area for the chance to observe this nocturnal creature, with the early mornings and late evenings being the best times for sightings. The Ulu Pandan region offers a serene environment for nature enthusiasts to enjoy this remarkable species in its natural habitat.
